WEBVTT

00:01.032 --> 00:03.574
Woman: WELCOME
TO THE WORK BENCH!

00:03.574 --> 00:04.575
HELLO!

00:04.575 --> 00:06.077
WELCOME TO
THE WORK BENCH.

00:06.077 --> 00:07.578
YOUR AURA
IS SO STRONG TODAY.

00:07.578 --> 00:10.111
JUST REALLY
BEAUTIFUL.

00:10.111 --> 00:11.682
GOOD FOR YOU!

00:11.682 --> 00:13.714
WHAT IS THAT?
NEW GREETER.

00:13.714 --> 00:15.146
WELCOME TO
THE WORK BENCH.
AHH!

00:15.146 --> 00:17.088
YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU NEED HELP.

00:17.088 --> 00:19.019
UH, NO,
WE WORK HERE.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.591
THAT IS SO GREAT!

00:20.591 --> 00:24.495
I'M MARY PAT.
I JUST STARTED
TODAY.

00:24.495 --> 00:25.756
GROUP HUG!

00:25.756 --> 00:28.028
NO.

00:29.060 --> 00:32.403
SHE'S LIKE THAT GUM
THAT BURSTS THAT STUFF
IN YOUR MOUTH.

00:32.403 --> 00:34.265
FLAVOR?
YEAH, EXACTLY.

00:34.265 --> 00:36.067
I HATE THAT GUM.

00:36.067 --> 00:36.737
ANY WORD FROM TONY?

00:36.737 --> 00:37.768
NO, I CAN'T GET
A HOLD OF HIM.

00:37.768 --> 00:40.111
YOU SURE HE'LL BE ABLE
TO TRANSLATE
THE INCANTATION?

00:40.111 --> 00:42.473
TONY'S BEEN A DEMON
SINCE THE ORIGINAL FALL.

00:42.473 --> 00:43.674
IF ANYONE CAN, IT'S HIM.

00:43.674 --> 00:45.076
YEAH, HE CAN.
I MEAN, HE HAS TO.

00:45.076 --> 00:48.048
OH, MY APRON'S
IN THE STOCKROOM.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

00:48.048 --> 00:49.320
ALL RIGHT.

00:49.320 --> 00:52.052
[CIRCUS MUSIC PLAYING]

01:04.165 --> 01:06.066
IT'S SO SAD.

01:06.066 --> 01:09.770
TAKEN SO YOUNG,
SO FULL OF LIFE.

01:09.770 --> 01:12.503
[TURNS OFF MUSIC]
WHO, THE MONKEY?

01:12.503 --> 01:14.605
THEY CALLED HIM
JIMBO.

01:14.605 --> 01:17.348
JIMBO
THE DANCING MONKEY.

01:17.348 --> 01:18.779
ANY TIME I FELT
A BIT BLUE,

01:18.779 --> 01:20.851
I'D COME AND WATCH
JIMBO DANCE,

01:20.851 --> 01:22.583
DANCE THAT
MONKEY DANCE.

01:22.583 --> 01:24.555
HE WAS EVEN TAUGHT
TO PICK POCKETS.

01:24.555 --> 01:26.787
SO MULTI-TALENTED.

01:26.787 --> 01:28.319
SORRY?

01:28.319 --> 01:31.392
SO, UH, A NEW SOUL?

01:34.265 --> 01:36.297
SAM?
YEAH?

01:36.297 --> 01:38.469
I NEED MY JIMBO FIX.

01:38.469 --> 01:40.801
I WANT YOU TO DANCE
LIKE A MONKEY.

01:40.801 --> 01:42.203
NO.
YES!

01:42.203 --> 01:43.774
I WANT YOU
TO PUT ON THIS FEZ

01:43.774 --> 01:46.237
AND DANCE
LIKE JIMBO.

01:46.237 --> 01:46.877
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR SKULL.

01:46.877 --> 01:48.108
I'M NOT DOING
A MONKEY DANCE FOR YOU.

01:48.108 --> 01:51.111
PERHAPS YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND THE EXACT
NATURE OF OUR RELATIONSHIP.

01:51.111 --> 01:54.245
I OWN YOU.
WHEN I ASK YOU
TO DO SOMETHING,

01:54.245 --> 01:54.885
YOU JUST DO IT.

01:54.885 --> 01:57.748
THAT SIMPLE.
[CHUCKLES]

02:01.252 --> 02:03.154
[LAUGHS]

02:03.154 --> 02:05.756
I HATE YOU.
I KNOW.

02:05.756 --> 02:08.699
[CIRCUS MUSIC PLAYING]
DANCE, MONKEY,

02:08.699 --> 02:10.861
DANCE!

02:10.861 --> 02:13.734
[LAUGHS]

02:15.206 --> 02:16.167
OH, COME ON!

02:16.167 --> 02:18.869
PUT YOUR HEART
AND SOUL
INTO IT, MAN!

02:18.869 --> 02:20.371
HA HA HA!

02:20.371 --> 02:22.343
DANCE LIKE
YOUR LIFE
DEPENDS UPON IT!

02:22.343 --> 02:23.574
IT DOES!

02:23.574 --> 02:25.616
[LAUGHS]

02:25.616 --> 02:26.917
HA HA, YES!
MONKEY DANCE!

02:26.917 --> 02:30.821
HE'S DOING
THE MONKEY DANCE!

02:38.859 --> 02:40.561
WELCOME TO THE WORK BENCH!

02:40.561 --> 02:43.194
HAVE A FANTASTIC DAY!

02:43.694 --> 02:46.367
FIRST HE STICKS ME
WITH A SUCKY SOUL
ASSIGNMENT,

02:46.367 --> 02:47.698
AND THEN HE MAKES ME
DANCE LIKE A MONKEY?

02:47.698 --> 02:50.701
YEAH, I'M AFRAID I GOTTA
SIDE WITH THE DEVIL
ON THAT ONE, SAMMY.

02:50.701 --> 02:53.304
SOUNDED LIKE
A PRETTY SPECIAL MONKEY.

02:53.304 --> 02:54.875
THANKS FOR
UNDERSTANDING.

02:54.875 --> 02:55.776
YOU GOT IT.

02:55.776 --> 02:57.848
SOUL IS ROGER LUND.

02:57.848 --> 03:00.351
SAYS HERE
HE'S A DRUG DEALER.

03:01.482 --> 03:02.653
WHOA!

03:02.653 --> 03:04.955
MUST BE PRETTY
BAD ASS TO NEED THIS.

03:04.955 --> 03:06.587
YEAH. SPEAKING OF BAD ASS,

03:06.587 --> 03:08.789
YOU ARE ABOUT TO WITNESS
THE MAIDEN VOYAGE

03:08.789 --> 03:12.192
OF THE COLOR-BLENDO 3000
PAINT MIXER.

03:12.192 --> 03:13.694
WELL, DID YOU READ
THE INSTRUCTIONS?

03:13.694 --> 03:15.766
ALL I NEED IS
AN ON SWITCH, SAMMY.

03:15.766 --> 03:18.729
INSTRUCTIONS? PHHTT.

03:22.803 --> 03:25.536
HA HA!

03:34.715 --> 03:36.917
THAT WAS AWESOME.

03:37.818 --> 03:39.950
MARY PAT,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

03:39.950 --> 03:40.821
OF COURSE, SILLY.

03:40.821 --> 03:44.855
MY FAIRIES PUT THIS
LUCKY PENNY ON THE FLOOR.

03:44.855 --> 03:45.926
THEY SAVED ME.

03:45.926 --> 03:46.827
YOUR WHAT?

03:46.827 --> 03:50.431
MY FAIRIES.
THEY PROTECT ME FROM HARM.

03:50.731 --> 03:54.365
OH, WELCOME TO THE WORK BENCH!
HAVE A SPLENDID DAY!

03:54.365 --> 03:56.937
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

04:09.680 --> 04:11.682
UNIT 5,
THIS IS THE PLACE.

04:11.682 --> 04:13.023
Sock: THIS SOUL
IS A DRUG DEALER?

04:13.023 --> 04:14.585
OBVIOUSLY NOT
A VERY GOOD ONE.

04:14.585 --> 04:15.856
I EXPECTED IT
TO BE, YOU KNOW--

04:15.856 --> 04:18.028
SWANKIER?
YEAH, MORE SWANK.

04:18.028 --> 04:19.560
HEY, WHOA,
WHERE DID YOU GET THOSE?

04:19.560 --> 04:21.692
HUH? BENCH,
GARDENING SECTION.

04:21.692 --> 04:24.395
REASONABLY PRICED.

04:26.567 --> 04:28.769
OW!

04:30.471 --> 04:32.903
[FROG CROAKING]

04:37.678 --> 04:40.681
[ROGER LAUGHING]

04:40.681 --> 04:43.053
HEY.
HEY.

04:43.053 --> 04:45.756
ARE YOU HUNTING BUFFALO
OR SOMETHING?

04:45.756 --> 04:47.688
WE'RE HERE TO SEND YOU
BACK TO HELL.

04:47.688 --> 04:50.791
OH, NO, MAN.

04:50.791 --> 04:51.622
THAT IS TRAGIC!

04:51.622 --> 04:54.595
WAIT, JUST LET ME GET
MY TICKLE ON FIRST.

04:54.595 --> 04:56.767
HIS TICKLE, MAN.
HIS MELLOW.

04:56.767 --> 04:59.600
SHAKE HANDS WITH ZEUS,
RIDE ON THE WAVY TRAIN.

04:59.600 --> 05:01.372
STORMING THE GATES
AT MORDOR.

05:01.372 --> 05:02.703
HE WANTS TO GET HIGH.

05:02.703 --> 05:03.734
JUST SAY NO.

05:03.734 --> 05:05.936
OH, MAN,
DON'T BE LIKE THAT.

05:05.936 --> 05:08.409
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
A COMPLETE DOWNER
HELL IS?

05:08.409 --> 05:11.041
I GOTTA BE WRECKED
TO FACE THAT AGAIN.

05:11.041 --> 05:12.443
PLEASE?

05:12.443 --> 05:14.615
ALL RIGHT, FINE.
JUST HURRY UP.

05:14.615 --> 05:15.586
[CHUCKLES]

05:15.586 --> 05:17.948
IF YOU WANT TO GET HIGH,

05:17.948 --> 05:19.350
YET KEEP YOUR BODY CLEAN,

05:19.350 --> 05:22.823
LICKING A TOAD
IS REALLY THE BEST WAY.

05:22.823 --> 05:25.956
UNLESS YOU GET
A POISON ONE.

05:25.956 --> 05:27.698
[FROG CROAKING]

05:27.698 --> 05:29.830
All: OOHH!

05:30.401 --> 05:32.503
NO. NO, THANK YOU.

05:33.364 --> 05:35.906
[ALL SCREAMING]

05:35.906 --> 05:37.408
SAM, SAM!

05:37.408 --> 05:38.669
GET HIM, BENJI!

05:38.669 --> 05:40.010
COME ON! SAMMY!

05:40.010 --> 05:42.873
[ALL YELLING]

05:42.873 --> 05:45.776
SOCK, THE VESSEL!

05:47.778 --> 05:50.020
[ALL YELLING]

05:50.020 --> 05:51.622
AAHH!

05:51.622 --> 05:52.883
[ALL PANTING]

05:52.883 --> 05:54.825
YEAH!

05:54.825 --> 05:56.787
WHOO! AHH.

05:57.528 --> 05:59.830
I THINK IT WAS LIKE A ROPE.

05:59.830 --> 06:00.891
LIKE A FIRE HOSE, YOU KNOW?

06:00.891 --> 06:04.134
YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT YOU CAN DO
WITH A LICKER LIKE THAT?

06:04.134 --> 06:05.466
BEYOND THE OBVIOUS, I MEAN?

06:05.466 --> 06:08.569
IT'S--NO, NO, WE ARE NOT
BRINGING THOSE HOME WITH US.

06:08.569 --> 06:12.603
WHAT--I DON'T WANT
THE DEATH OF INNOCENT
TOADS ON MY CONSCIENCE.

06:12.603 --> 06:12.903
DO YOU?

06:12.903 --> 06:15.746
ALL RIGHT, FINE,
FINE, BRING 'EM,
BRING 'EM.

06:15.746 --> 06:17.708
GREAT. THEN GET
THE OTHER TANKS.

06:17.708 --> 06:18.609
[GROANS]

06:18.609 --> 06:22.853
GREAT TIME TO MAKE
AN EXECUTIVE DECISION, SAM.

06:23.914 --> 06:25.716
KING CHARLIE,

06:25.716 --> 06:26.957
MEET THE PRINCE.

06:26.957 --> 06:28.989
NOW, YOU CAN KISS
THE PRINCE ALL DAY,

06:28.989 --> 06:33.724
BUT HE WILL ALWAYS
STAY SMALL, GREEN
AND UGLY,

06:33.724 --> 06:35.766
RIGHT?
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:35.766 --> 06:36.867
COMING.

06:36.867 --> 06:40.100
OK, COME ON NOW.

06:43.434 --> 06:44.475
HI, GRANDMA.

06:44.475 --> 06:45.405
HOLA, BENJAMIN.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.177
[STAMMERING]
COME IN, SIT DOWN.

06:47.177 --> 06:49.409
GRANDMA, HOW ARE YOU?
ARE YOU OK?

06:49.409 --> 06:50.681
HOW'S YOUR HEART?

06:50.681 --> 06:52.082
YOU LOOK GOOD.

06:52.082 --> 06:53.614
I LOOK LIKE GARBAGE.

06:53.614 --> 06:55.916
MY HEALTH
IS AILING, MIJO.

06:55.916 --> 06:57.848
I FEAR I'M NOT LONG
FOR THIS WORLD.

06:57.848 --> 06:59.490
OH, DON'T SAY THAT, GRANDMA.

06:59.490 --> 07:01.892
BUT UNTIL
THAT TIME COMES,

07:01.892 --> 07:03.694
I WANT TO TIE UP
LOOSE ENDS

07:03.694 --> 07:08.699
AND APOLOGIZE FOR
THE WAY I TREATED
YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

07:08.699 --> 07:09.029
HMM.

07:09.029 --> 07:12.432
I'M INVITING YOU TO
DINNER AT MY HOUSE.

07:12.432 --> 07:15.205
BOTH YOU AND NINA.
REALLY?

07:15.205 --> 07:18.669
I DON'T WANT
TO LEAVE THIS WORLD
WITH REGRETS.

07:18.669 --> 07:21.842
OK, YEAH, YEAH,
WE'LL COME TO DINNER.

07:21.842 --> 07:25.145
[FROG CROAKING]

07:26.016 --> 07:26.747
OOOH.

07:26.747 --> 07:28.779
WHAT IS THIS,
A ZOO?

07:33.524 --> 07:34.454
HEY.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.557
ANY LUCK FINDING OUT
WHAT THE SYMBOLS MEAN?

07:36.557 --> 07:37.588
NOT EVEN CLOSE.

07:37.588 --> 07:41.562
I GUESS THESE SYMBOLS
REALLY ARE OLDER
THAN LANGUAGE.

07:41.562 --> 07:42.563
COOL!

07:42.563 --> 07:45.135
YOU GUYS INTO MAGIK
WITH A "K", TOO?

07:45.135 --> 07:48.468
MY FAIRIES GOT ME
BELIEVING IN ALL
THINGS SUPERNATURAL.

07:48.468 --> 07:49.700
YOUR FAIRIES?

07:49.700 --> 07:51.201
OH, THEY SAVE ME
FROM EVERYTHING.

07:51.201 --> 07:52.142
ALWAYS LOOKING OUT
FOR ME.

07:52.142 --> 07:56.176
JUST WISH THEY'D
SAVE ME FROM MYSELF,
FILTHY HABIT.

07:56.176 --> 07:59.780
HAVE SUPER FUN
WITH YOUR BOOK
ON THE OCCULT!

08:02.853 --> 08:03.714
SHE'S SWEET.

08:03.714 --> 08:06.086
IN A CRAZY, CHUCKY
CHEESE ANIMATRONIC

08:06.086 --> 08:08.258
CREATURE
KIND OF WAY.

08:08.258 --> 08:09.920
[FLICKING LIGHTER]

08:09.920 --> 08:12.763
IS SHE SMOKING OUT
BY THE PROPANE TANKS?

08:12.763 --> 08:15.526
[EXPLOSION]

08:25.876 --> 08:28.138
OH, MY GOD.

08:29.640 --> 08:30.881
MARY PAT!

08:30.881 --> 08:32.512
ARE YOU OK?

08:32.512 --> 08:34.044
AM I ALL RIGHT?

08:34.044 --> 08:35.215
YEAH.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.647
I'M...

08:36.647 --> 08:37.748
INCREDIBLE!

08:37.748 --> 08:42.953
I WAS SURROUNDED
BY THE HEAVENLY WARMTH
OF A HUNDRED FAIRIES!

08:42.953 --> 08:44.855
MESSAGE RECEIVED!

08:44.855 --> 08:46.296
THAT'S MY LAST
CIGARETTE EVER!

08:46.296 --> 08:50.530
OK, WE NEED TO
GET YOU LOOKED
AT. COME ON.

08:57.938 --> 09:00.310
THE BLAST WENT AROUND HER?

09:00.310 --> 09:02.913
SHE REALLY WAS
PROTECTED BY A FAIRY.

09:02.913 --> 09:06.647
NOW, SAM!

09:06.647 --> 09:07.878
A FAIRY?

09:07.878 --> 09:08.849
STEVE?

09:08.849 --> 09:10.320
DO I LOOK LIKE
A FAIRY TO YOU?

09:10.320 --> 09:11.682
OOP, DON'T ANSWER THAT!

09:11.682 --> 09:15.185
COME HERE! [LAUGHING]

09:26.637 --> 09:27.337
I JUST KEEP
TELLING MYSELF,

09:27.337 --> 09:28.568
YOU GOTTA START
AT THE BOTTOM, STEVE.

09:28.568 --> 09:31.171
EVEN THOUGH
YOU WERE AMONG
THE HOLIEST OF HOSTS,

09:31.171 --> 09:34.344
EVEN THOUGH GUARDIAN ANGEL
DUTY IS SUPER ENTRY LEVEL

09:34.344 --> 09:37.708
AND COMPLETELY BENEATH ME,
RISE ABOVE.

09:37.708 --> 09:39.810
DIGNITY, CLASS, BEAUTY--

09:39.810 --> 09:41.612
THAT IS MY MANTRA.

09:41.612 --> 09:42.352
GREAT.
LISTEN, STEVE--

09:42.352 --> 09:44.284
SO, THESE DAYS I JUST
SPEND MY TIME

09:44.284 --> 09:46.586
PROTECTING
THAT FAIRY-LOVING WACKO

09:46.586 --> 09:48.158
FROM KILLING HERSELF.

09:48.158 --> 09:49.289
JUST A STEPPING STONE.

09:49.289 --> 09:54.795
JUST A WEIRD, CRAZY,
ACCIDENT-PRONE
STEPPING STONE

09:54.795 --> 09:55.726
WITH NO FASHION SENSE.

09:55.726 --> 09:57.628
HEY, STEVE,
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE TONY IS?

09:57.628 --> 10:01.371
YES, I DO. HE IS AT A SPA
IN TAHOE WITH LITTLE STEVIE.

10:01.371 --> 10:04.034
IT IS THIS WONDERFUL PLACE
WE USED TO GO TO.

10:04.034 --> 10:04.975
YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?

10:04.975 --> 10:05.936
THEY JUST--
THEY BOTH NEED

10:05.936 --> 10:07.077
A LITTLE BIT
OF PAMPERING THESE DAYS.

10:07.077 --> 10:10.140
DAMN IT. I NEED HIM
TO TRANSLATE SOMETHING.

10:10.140 --> 10:11.141
HMM.

10:11.141 --> 10:12.142
YOU KNOW WHAT,

10:12.142 --> 10:14.344
MAYBE YOU COULD DO IT.

10:14.985 --> 10:16.887
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?

10:16.887 --> 10:19.119
WE COPIED IT
FROM A SCROLL
MY DAD FOUND IN HELL.

10:19.119 --> 10:21.852
NINA SAYS IT'S
AN OLD DEMON LANGUAGE.

10:21.852 --> 10:22.823
YEAH.

10:22.823 --> 10:24.224
CAN YOU READ IT?

10:24.224 --> 10:24.955
OH, WELL, I MEAN,

10:24.955 --> 10:28.128
TONY WAS REALLY MORE
THE READER IN THE RELATIONSHIP,

10:28.128 --> 10:29.299
BUT, UM,

10:29.299 --> 10:31.161
I THINK I CAN TRANSLATE.

10:31.161 --> 10:32.332
GREAT! THAT'S GREAT.
WHAT DOES IT SAY?

10:32.332 --> 10:36.867
OK, WELL, I BELIEVE
THIS IS AN INCANTATION

10:36.867 --> 10:39.970
SUMMONING THE DEVIL INTO

10:39.970 --> 10:41.712
A CONTEST.
YES!

10:41.712 --> 10:43.313
YEAH! THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT IT IS.

10:43.313 --> 10:44.314
YEAH.
OK, HOW DO I DO IT?

10:44.314 --> 10:47.217
OK, WELL, YOU HAVE
TO SAY THESE WORDS EXACTLY,

10:47.217 --> 10:48.118
AND THEN HE'LL APPEAR,

10:48.118 --> 10:52.883
AND THEN HE IS COMPELLED
TO COMPETE IN A CONTEST
THAT YOU CHOOSE.

10:52.883 --> 10:54.685
IF YOU GIVE ME A DAY,
I CAN WRITE DOWN

10:54.685 --> 10:56.256
A PHONETIC
PRONUNCIATION FOR YOU.

10:56.256 --> 10:57.858
THANK YOU, THANK YOU!
YOU ARE AMAZING.

10:57.858 --> 11:00.090
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT THIS MEANS TO ME.

11:00.090 --> 11:02.362
UM...

11:02.362 --> 11:04.394
WHAT CONTEST
SHOULD I DO?

11:04.394 --> 11:05.295
THAT DEPENDS ON YOU, SAM.

11:05.295 --> 11:08.298
I MEAN, IT'S, YOU KNOW,
IT'S WHATEVER YOU'RE GOOD AT.

11:08.298 --> 11:11.141
RIGHT, RIGHT.
WHAT I'M GOOD AT.

11:11.141 --> 11:12.903
YEAH.

11:12.903 --> 11:15.846
SAM? SAM, COME ON, SAM.

11:15.846 --> 11:17.778
EVERYBODY'S
GOOD AT SOMETHING.

11:17.778 --> 11:19.449
YOU ARE...

11:19.449 --> 11:21.882
IN SHAPE.

11:21.882 --> 11:22.883
SPORTS?

11:22.883 --> 11:23.954
NO, I'M TERRIBLE.

11:23.954 --> 11:26.957
OK. UM, MATH?
EVEN WORSE.

11:26.957 --> 11:28.358
MOVING ON TO THE ARTS.

11:28.358 --> 11:30.791
PICTIONARY!

11:30.791 --> 11:31.291
NEVER PLAYED IT.

11:31.291 --> 11:33.363
SOUNDS TOO MUCH
LIKE "DICTIONARY."

11:33.363 --> 11:35.265
MUSIC.

11:35.265 --> 11:37.197
YES!

11:37.197 --> 11:39.329
THAT'S IT!
THAT IS IT.

11:39.329 --> 11:41.301
YOU'RE A GENIUS!

11:44.334 --> 11:45.375
SO WHAT IS ALL THIS STUFF?

11:45.375 --> 11:48.839
SOME STUFF MY MOM SAVED
FROM ELEMENTARY SCHOOL.

11:48.839 --> 11:50.380
AHA, THIS IS IT.

11:50.380 --> 11:52.382
MY TICKET
OUT OF MY DEAL
WITH THE DEVIL.

11:52.382 --> 11:55.345
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU PLAYED
A MUSICAL INSTRUMENT, SAM.

11:55.345 --> 11:56.046
YEAH, NEITHER DID I.

11:56.046 --> 11:58.949
YEAH. IN THIRD GRADE,
MRS. WARD SAID I WAS
THE BEST IN THE CLASS.

11:58.949 --> 12:00.420
SHE MADE ME FIRST CHAIR
IN THE SCHOOL ORCHESTRA.

12:00.420 --> 12:01.852
I WAS BETTER THAN
THE FOURTH GRADERS.

12:01.852 --> 12:04.324
ALL RIGHT, SAMMY,
LET'S HEAR A LITTLE ZEP.

12:04.324 --> 12:05.255
I HAVEN'T PLAYED
IN A WHILE,

12:05.255 --> 12:07.457
BUT IT SHOULD BE
LIKE RIDING
A BIKE, RIGHT?

12:07.457 --> 12:08.999
TOTALLY.

12:08.999 --> 12:12.102
[PLAYING MARY HAD
A LITTLE LAMB]

12:14.064 --> 12:16.006
THERE HE IS.

12:16.006 --> 12:17.737
UH-HUH.

12:22.142 --> 12:25.245
OK, NOW BRING IT BACK,
BRING IT BACK.

12:25.245 --> 12:26.917
[SOCK HUMMING]

12:26.917 --> 12:28.248
YEAH!

12:28.248 --> 12:29.279
YEAH!

12:29.279 --> 12:31.321
ALL RIGHT, SAMMY,
YOU ARE GOOD AT SOMETHING.

12:31.321 --> 12:33.323
RIGHT, RIGHT,
RIGHT? SEE, I THINK
I CAN DO THIS!

12:33.323 --> 12:35.385
Sock: I THINK
YOU GOT IT.

12:36.026 --> 12:38.959
[PLAYING ROMANCE BY MOZART]

12:50.170 --> 12:51.401
